---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';

const title = "ADA Compliance Striping Springfield MO | Accessible Parking Lot Markings";
const description = "ADA-compliant parking lot striping in Springfield MO. We connect you with certified contractors for accessible stalls, van spaces, access aisles, and full compliance documentation.";
const h1 = "ADA Compliance Striping in Springfield, Missouri";
---

<ServiceLayout {title} {description} {h1}>
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-concrete leading-relaxed">
    <p class="text-xl">We connect facility managers and property owners in Springfield with certified contractors who specialize in ADA-compliant parking lot striping. Many Springfield properties need updated accessible stalls, properly sized access aisles, and clear documentation to meet current federal standards.</p>
    
    <p>We connect you with contractors who understand how to assess existing conditions and deliver compliant striping with proper photographic and measurement records.</p>

    <h2>ADA Striping Services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Correctly sized accessible stalls and van-accessible spaces</li>
      <li>Proper access aisle placement and dimensions</li>
      <li>High-visibility access aisle striping</li>
      <li>ADA-compliant directional markings</li>
      <li>Full compliance documentation for inspections</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Typical Cost Ranges</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>ADA compliance refresh (small–medium lot):</strong> $800 – $2,500</li>
      <li><strong>Full accessible stall redesign:</strong> $1,800 – $4,500</li>
      <li><strong>Van-accessible space + access aisle:</strong> $450 – $950 per space</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    
    <h3>How many accessible spaces are required?</h3>
    <p>Requirements are based on total number of stalls. For example, lots with 1–25 stalls need at least 1 accessible space; larger lots require a higher percentage plus van-accessible spaces.</p>

    <h3>Do you provide documentation for inspections?</h3>
    <p>Yes. All ADA projects include before-and-after photos, measurements, and stall counts suitable for city inspections and insurance records.</p>

    <h3>Can ADA work be done without closing the lot?</h3>
    <p>In most cases, yes. Work is typically done in sections or during off-peak hours.</p>
  </div>

    <h2>Related Service Areas</h2>
    <p>We also serve <a href="/service-area/republic-mo">Republic</a>, <a href="/service-area/nixa-mo">Nixa</a>, <a href="/service-area/ozark-mo">Ozark</a>, <a href="/service-area/battlefield-mo">Battlefield</a>, and <a href="/service-area/rogersville-mo">Rogersville</a>.</p>
</ServiceLayout>